<br>
Base = 1120<br>
Bracer (20% parsed) = 1120 * 0.2 = 224<br>
Extra Crit Damage = (at 50%) = 1120 * 0.5 =560<br>
                            (at 54%) = 1120 * 0.54 = 604.8<br>
                            (at 55%) = 1120 * 0.55 = 616<br>
--------------------------------------------------<br>
First total = 1904<br>
Second total = 1948.8<br>
Third Total = 1960<br>
<br>
Third total there, which is assuming a 55% innate crit with 20% bracer shows that max damage would actually be 10 higher than what was found.  It is entirely possible that 55% is the max crit percentage, the difference between it and 50% would probably not have been enough to notice on the Draughts most of us would have used for the initial testing.  If it's within 5%, testing with a big boomer would probably give more consistent results than with a less damaging spell, and would also prohibit finding this out until now, as who's gonna blow that much mana chaining Ice Comets trying for that 2% crit chance?<br>
